  "coverage": "DEBT_SECURITIES_ONLY; haven equity VIEs/ADRs not in IDS (equity nationality gap)",
  "coverage_note": "BIS IDS (WS_DEBT_SEC2_PUB) covers DEBT securities only. The haven-resident equity structures of Chinese firms \u2014 Cayman/BVI-incorporated VIEs and US-listed ADRs (e.g. Alibaba, Tencent, PDD, Baidu) \u2014 are EQUITY and are NOT in IDS. The nationality-basis marginal grounded here is therefore a DEBT marginal. Equity issuance reattributed to Chinese nationality is NOT covered by this source and must be sourced elsewhere (e.g. equity datasets); it is an explicit coverage gap, not assumed zero.",
  "confidence": "HIGH",
  "confidence_reason": "Both series fetched live from the BIS SDMX REST API on 2026-06-30 (HTTP 200). Nationality basis confirmed from the dataset's own dimension labels in the fetched v2 labelled CSV ('Issuer nationality' = CN = China; ISSUER_RES=3P 'All countries excluding residents'), not from memory. Amounts-outstanding (MEASURE=I), USD, millions, quarterly all read from fetched metadata. Nationality (~$1.13T) vs residence (~$211B) ~5x gap is consistent with reattribution of haven-resident issuance to the Chinese parent.",
